// ============================================
// INSTALLATION TIPS
// ============================================
// 1. Global install (recommended):
//    npm install -g @modelcontextprotocol/server-name
//    Then use: "command": "mcp-server-name"
//
// 2. Replace 'username' with your actual username
//
// 3. Never commit API keys! Use environment variables:
//    "env": {"KEY": "${ENV_VAR_NAME}"}
//
// 4. Start with: filesystem, memory, fetch
//    Then add others as needed
//
// 5. Check logs if server fails:
//    Check MCP client logs for error details
//
// 6. Test individual servers:
//    npx @modelcontextprotocol/server-name --help

// ============================================
// SECURITY BEST PRACTICES
// ============================================
// - Filesystem: Only whitelist necessary directories
// - GitHub: Use tokens with minimal required scopes
// - Postgres: Create read-only user for queries
// - APIs: Use environment variables, never hardcode keys
// - Git: Consider read-only mode for safety
// - Docker: Limit to inspection, not modification
